VA violin virtuoso
p3
sVnews
p4
VFormer Principal of M.R. Govt. College of Music and Dance, Vizianagaram, Dwaram Durgaprasada Rao, supported by his younger brother Satyanarayana (AIR Staffer at Hyderabad) on the violin and in the company of mridangam maestro V. Kamalakara Rao (Rajahmundry) and his disciple Mangalagiri Sridhar on the ghatam, rendered violin solo on the premises of Sri Sankara Matham on Monday.The concert was organised by Sri Vijaya Thyagaraja Sangeetha Sabha as part of birth centenary celebrations of his father, violin maestro Dwaram Narasingarao Naidu.Rendering the recital, Prasada Rao proved himself a worthyfollower of the legacy of  his father.Getting off to a tunefully brisk start withSaveri varnam, he played all compositions of Thyagaraja,Ninuvina(Navarasakannada) andKannatandrinaapai(Devamanohari), both adorned with exquisite raga and swara essays, before he went in for expansive expatiation ofNadopasana(Begada).It was marked with scholarly weaving of innovative phraseology instantly in the raga essay andgathibhedaminswarakalpanain the two tempos.While Satyanarayana lent fortifying support, Kamalakara Rao turned out to be his peer, unfolding soul-ticklinglaya bhavaevolved by his great guru Palghat Mani, besides going innovative both in his following and turns, executing a vibratingthani.His disciple, Mangalagiri Sridhar, on the ghatam lent invigorating support.The playing ofJagadodharana(Kapi) of Purandaradasa,Raghuvamsa Sudhambudhichandra(Kadanakuthuhalam) of Patnam Subrahmanya Iyer and a string of folk and western tunes marked the tailpiece.
